After a fire broke out in Letaba Rest Camp in the Kruger National Park (KNP) on Wednesday evening, the park kept the public up to date on the situation with a series of tweets from its Twitter account. The series of event were relayed as follows: ALSO READ: Poverty-stricken community of Zwelishane Trust left without clean water Lastly, the park sent the following message out this morning. “This morning guests and staff are waking up to a horrible sight of the burned TV room and shop at Letaba Rest Camp. The fire was finally brought under control this morning without any casualties. Well done to all involved. Investigations into the cause of the fire have commenced.” 